{
  "id": "6e9e0974e36a4e4c939cc5bf879903e5",
  "title": "Universal Options V2.3!",
  "description": "Data-Driven, expandable framework for all your game settings. Advanced Options System with a Modular Menu! Modular design, and Modular Widgets. Enhanced Input, Platform, System settings, and more!",
  "longDescription": "<p>V2 Release Date: December 2022</p><p>V2.1 Release Date: January 2023</p><p>V2.2 Release Date: July 2023</p><p>V2.3 Release Date: April 2024</p><p><br /></p><p>Now With platform-sensitive settings and overrides for even more flexibility!</p><p><br /></p><p>As new significant features get added on and on, the price may increase in the future. Get it now, and enjoy the updates to come!</p><p><br /></p><p><a href=\"https://discord.gg/7ARv62rUum\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discord</a></p><p><a href=\"https://github.com/FunderburkM/CMEngineOptionsDocs\" rel=\"nofollow\">Documentation: Link</a> [V2 and V1]</p><p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list&#61;PLybwJiY_V7EE8fHECPGtVyQkWW2Tn8mHj\" rel=\"nofollow\">Youtube Playlist (Overviews, Updates, Implementation)</a> [V1]</p><p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/16SRHBlQJdJcamcISwTUcFHT6MKPjcV56/view?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">Example Project</a>[V1.0]</p><p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Z4rACdRBbrlpsBFQkgccj00SPhD4Fj6N/view?usp&#61;share_link\" rel=\"nofollow\">Example Project</a>[V2.1]</p><p><br /></p><p>Approach Game Settings in an entirely new way. Powered by Data Assets and Modular Framework, Universal Options gives you the power, ease of setup, and flexibility that your game needs. Easily set up your settings, your widgets, and even game settings that can affect your gameplay! Ready to Plug and play with your Main Menu, options system houses a full environment for all your graphic, sound/audio, input, and game settings! Switch Monitors/Screens, Output Headphones/Speakers/Devices, rebind standard and enhanced input key mappings, and much more. Professionally made, ready to power your full projects!</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>General Features</p><ul><li>Data-Driven settings, no code required for plugin setup</li><li>Modular Settings framework</li><li>Full blueprint Support</li><li>Full Widget, Component, and Listener system for easy integration</li><li>Modular Widget Framework, Dynamic Widget Generation</li><li>JSON-based settings, extensive JSON additional features</li><li>Advanced support for SaveGame Properties</li><li>Platform Settings, System Settings, and now with Steam Deck Support</li></ul><p>Graphic Settings Features</p><ul><li>Scalability Settings</li><li>Resolution and Window settings</li><li>Monitor Switching</li></ul><p>Sound Setting Features</p><ul><li>Sound class and Mix control</li><li>Sound device switching</li></ul><p>Input Setting Features</p><ul><li>Dynamic Rebinding</li><li>Multi-input profile</li><li>Rebinding keys with modifiers</li><li>Display data for Keys (text and textures)</li><li>Enhanced input rebinding</li><li>Controller Detection and Auto-Switching Support</li></ul><p>Game Setting Features</p><ul><li>Make your own game settings and save them to disk</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>Code Modules:</p><ul><li>Â CM_Engine_Options [Runtime]</li><li>UniversalOptions (Runtime)</li><li>UniversalOptionsEditor (Editor)</li></ul><p>Number of Blueprints: 78 (v1), 75&#43; (v2)</p><p>Number of C&#43;&#43; Classes (v1 and v2): 180&#43; classes &amp; structs, 60&#43; enumerators</p><p>Network Replicated: Features are Network Adequate. The system works locally on a Game Instance Subsystem</p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Windows, Linux, Mac, IOS, Android</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: Windows, Linux, Mac, IOS, Android</p>",
